        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 25 at 3:42PM CDT by NWS Birmingham AL</headline>
        <description>At 341 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Trafford, or 9 miles north of Gardendale, moving northeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Nectar, Hayden, Trafford, Warrior, Palmerdale, County Line, Smoke
Rise, Holly Springs, Village Springs, Locust Fork, Remlap, Fairview,
Inland Lake, Gardendale, Kimberly, Clear Springs, Morris, Dallas,
Allgood, and Springville.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
